I just wanted to make a suggestion on route handlers, it seems wasteful to me to have to re-define routes in order to handle different functionality for different HTTP methods. For example, the docs have:

```python
@app.route('/myview', methods=['POST'])
def myview_post():
    pass

@app.route('/myview', methods=['PUT'])
def myview_put():
    pass
```

From what I can tell the function names are arbitrary, my suggestion would be to allow implicit method support through explicit function names, examples being how https://falconframework.org/ does it using `on_get`, `on_post`, etc as function names within a Resource class.

