If you don't have read permission to the bucket containing a collection you have read access for, you can't see that bucket listed anywhere it seems. In an ideal world, I'd expect that if I have access to `/buckets/buck/collections/coll`:

- I could query `/buckets` and see `buck` listed;
- I could query `/buckets/buck/collections` and see `coll` listed.

Silly thoughts: 

- Maybe we need a new `enumerate` permission type?
- Maybe we need a new endpoint (possibly through a plugin) allowing to retrieve the tree of available resources for a given authenticated user? eg.

```
$ http http://kinto/v1/access
